Nation Nyoka, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A group of men stole merchandise worth over R100 000 from two stores in the Pinecrest mall in Pinetown, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Wednesday.Two men were caught on security cameras breaking open the mall&rsquo;s entrance doors on Tuesday night, spokesperson Warrant Officer Muzi Mahumapelo said.Three other men carrying bags joined them and they proceeded to smash the display windows of the Foschini and Watches 4 U stores, where they helped themselves to clothing and jewellery.They fled in a BMW with a Gauteng registration number.Anyone with information about the robbery could contact Pinetown police on 031-325-5062. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.